******
[2] Cholera - Ghana (Accra)
Date: Fri 1 Aug 2014
Source: GhanaWeb, TV3 report [edited]
http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/health/artikel.php?ID=319450


Authorities at the La General Hospital in Accra have been forced to turn the out-patient department (OPD) of the hospital into a cholera bay as a result of soaring numbers in recorded cases. TV3 gathers that as of Friday, 1 Aug 2014, 15 new cases of the bacterial disease was recorded at the hospital.

Speaking to our correspondent on Friday, Dr Samuel Asamoah, the hospital's Physician Assistant, said the major challenge facing the hospital is space. "We don't have anywhere to send the patients back," he noted, however. He observed that most of the patients brought to the hospital are from the La municipality, generating worry in the face of an epidemic.

