[3] Cholera - Nigeria (Borno State)
Date: Fri 1 Aug 2014
Source: AllAfrica, CAJ News report [edited]
http://allafrica.com/stories/201408010932.html


A total of 8 people have reportedly died following a cholera outbreak at an internally displaced persons (IDPs) camp located at Biu in Borno State. The Red Cross reported that the epidemic had affected over 100 people out of the 10 000 IDPs at the camp.

A Red Cross official, under the condition of anonymity, told journalists that about 30 persons out of the initial 100 affected by the disease have so far fully recovered. He said others are gradually recovering and responding to treatment being offered by the joint team of the Borno state health workers, National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) and Red Cross Society of Nigeria at the camp.

According to the official, the situation at the camp was made worse with Borno State not making available inadequate drugs and vaccination on the camp, but the medical team and other auxiliary team at the camp have been doing their best in controlling and treating the cholera outbreak.

Ministry of Health officials declined to comment. Borno State Commissioner of Health, Dr Salma Anas Kolo, could not be reached for comment.

[Byline: Augustine Osayande]

