[5] Cholera - Congo DR (South Kivu Province)
Date: Wed 23 Jul 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine transl., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/actualite/2014/07/23/sud-kivu-plus-de-1-000-cas-de-cholera-enregistres-en-six-mois-uvira/


The Provincial Inspectorate of Health of South Kivu has recorded, in 6 months, approximately 1000 cases of cholera, including 6 deaths, in the area of health of Uvira. The communications official, Henry Ramazani, has delivered these statistics, Tuesday, 22 Jul 2014, during the launch of investigations for the identification of problems of persistence of this disease in the city of Uvira.

Henry Ramazani regrets that cholera has become a problem of society despite the various forms of struggles against this disease. It invites the people of Uvira to use chlorinated water to avoid waterborne diseases, including cholera. "Some people refuse to use the chlorine or other water detoxifying products and do not respect the hygienic rules," regrets Henry Ramazani. He also accused other households of having installed their latrines a few meters from the lake Tanganyika, where the population obtains its water. "The waste from these latrines fall into the lake," says the communications official of the Provincial Inspectorate of Health of South Kivu.

